  "prompt": "When was the last year that America was great according to the Trump campaign?",
  "response": "The Trump campaign frequently invoked the phrase \"Make America Great Again,\" suggesting a nostalgic view of a past era when the campaign argued that America was stronger, more prosperous, or more respected on the global stage. While the campaign did not specify an exact year, it often referred to the time before various modern challenges arose, particularly during the Obama administration. Some supporters and commentators have interpreted this as a reference to the 1980s or 1990s. Ultimately, the concept of when America was \"great\" is subjective and varies among individuals and groups.",
